 BY LINUS CHIBUIKE FORMER Deputy Speaker of the House of Representatives, Babangida Nguroje, on Saturday night, lost seven members of his family in a road accident. The accident was said to have occurred along the Akwanga-Keffi Road, in Nasarawa State. Nguroje’s two sisters, Zainab and Hadiza, their four children, and one of the sisters’ husbands, all perished in the unfortunate accident, THE POINT learnt. President Muhammadu Buhari, in his condolence message to the former deputy speaker, said, “I am lost for words to describe such multiple deaths in a single car accident in which family members perished. “I received the news of this tragedy with deep shock and grief, and wish to express my heartfelt sympathy and solidarity with you at this trying and painful moment.” The President however prayed to Allah to forgive the gentle souls of the deceased persons and comfort those they left behind.  